{"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPoolRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ThreadPoolRef","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib13ThreadPoolRefV","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ThreadPoolRef","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/threadpoolref"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThreadPoolRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A thread pool is useful when you wish to asynchronously fork out the execution of work","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and continue working in your own thread. If that will happen often, the overhead of starting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and destroying a thread each time might be too high. In such cases reusing already started","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads seems like a good idea. And it indeed is, but implementing this can be tedious"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and error-prone."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Therefore GLib provides thread pools for your convenience. An added advantage is, that the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads can be shared between the different subsystems of your program, when they are using GLib."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a new thread pool, you use [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.new"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is destroyed by [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.free"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to execute a certain task within a thread pool, use [method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.push","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get the current number of running threads you call [method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"To get the number of still unprocessed tasks you call [method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.unprocessed","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"To control the maximum number of threads for a thread pool, you use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_threads"},{"text":"]. and [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Finally you can control the number of unused threads, that are kept alive by GLib for future use.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The current number can be fetched with [func"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The maximum number can be controlled by [func"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_unused_threads"},{"text":"]. All currently unused threads","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be stopped by calling [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.stop_unused_threads"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/